later I think attributed directly to Hitler to try 
to cut the Allied forces in two and capture the port

00:02.377 --> 00:14.679
of Antwerp. So we were right along the way to LiÃ¨ge 
and Antwerp. So that's what presumably the grand

00:20.089 --> 00:26.140
strategy was. By that time, of course, the Germans 
really didn't have enough resources to pull off

00:26.440 --> 00:35.357
that sort of maneuver. They had far more success 
